      <div>
        <head xml:id="AOHenley_anonymousweather-d0e573">12. Signs foretelling weather</head>
        <div>
          <head xml:id="AOHenley_anonymousweather-d0e577" subtype="h2">12.1. Foretelling good weather.</head>
          <entry xml:id="AOHenley_anonymousweather-idp347088">
            <form>
              <orth>[còta]</orth>
            </form>
            <def>“An crochadh tu do chota orra [sic].” In reference to the moon. If you could hang your coat on the moon according to its shape then a good day was in prospect. If you could not then
              the opposite applied.</def>
          </entry>
        </div>
